org.knime.core.data

Interface DataValue

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AdapterValue, BinaryObjectDataValue, BitVectorValue, BitVectorValue, BooleanValue, BoundedValue, ByteVectorValue, CollectionDataValue, ComplexNumberValue, DateAndTimeValue, DoubleValue, FileStoreKeyDataValue, FuzzyIntervalValue, FuzzyNumberValue, ImageValue, IntervalValue, IntValue, ListDataValue, LongValue, MissingValue, NominalValue, PMMLValue, PNGImageValue, PortObjectValue, RWAdapterValue, SetDataValue, SparseListDataValue, StringValue, TimestampValue, XMLValue
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AdapterCell, BinaryObjectDataCell, BinaryObjectFileStoreDataCell, BitVectorCell, BlobDataCell, BlobWrapperDataCell, BooleanCell, ComplexNumberCell, DataCell, DataType.MissingCell, DateAndTimeCell, DenseBitVectorCell, DenseByteVectorCell, DoubleCell, FileStoreCell, FileStoreKeyDataCell, FuzzyIntervalCell, FuzzyNumberCell, InputRow.WildCardCell, IntCell, IntervalCell, ListCell, LongCell, MissingCell, PMMLBlobCell, PMMLCell, PMMLCellContent, PNGImageBlobCell, PNGImageCell, PortObjectCell, SetCell, SotaDoubleCell, SotaFuzzyCell, SparseBitVectorCell, SparseByteVectorCell, SparseListCell, StringCell, TimestampCell, XMLBlobCell, XMLCell, XMLCellContent

    public interface DataValue
    The interface all value interfaces of DataCells are derived from. DataCells implement different DataValue interfaces to allow access to generic (or complex) fields from the cell. Typically a DataValue brings along its own (set of) renderers, an icon (which is displayed in table column headers, for instance) and a comparator, which are all defined through the definition of a static member UTILITY.

    For more information regarding the definition of new DataCells see the package description and the manual on how to define new types, in particular the remarks on DataValue.

    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, University of Konstanz

    • Field Detail

      • UTILITY

        static final DataValue.UtilityFactory UTILITY
        Static singleton for meta description. This field is accessed via reflection in the DataType class. It is used to determine renderer, comparator, and icon. Sub-Interfaces will "override" this static member, if they desire to define own renderers, comparator, and/or icon.
